This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories as it deals with 3D object detection from LiDAR data for autonomous driving. It also involves machine learning techniques, which makes it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of learning from range view data, which involves contextual information, making it relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
